* 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFAF12BFF320C81D48EAB86" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1945" box="[151,430,1937,1964]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauvarovia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendizabali">Glauvarovia mendizabali</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAFB653AFFFAF12BFE110C81D08FAF5A" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFAF12BFE110C81D151AE1A" blockId="14.[132,775,1937,2028]" lastBlockId="14.[810,1456,215,880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
is known from the localities indicated in the description of the species, i.e., Taguerzimet = Taguerzimt, 24°07’19”N, 15°06’42”W (type locality), and Bu Kerch = Boukarche, 24°55’16”N, 14°44’23”W (MNCN); three additional specimens from the lower valley of the Oued Dra are preserved in the MNHN (
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFBCE0A07D645AD7B" author="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="419 - 435" part="4" refId="ref13223" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. &amp; DESCAMPS M. 1968. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.) 4 (2): 419 - 435." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]" type="journal article" year="1968">Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps 1968</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been collected however during three field trips (1944, 1945 and 1946: see infra), but these data were not considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFC4E0A67D05AADBB" author="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" box="[1003,1402,375,401]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="419 - 435" part="4" refId="ref13223" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. &amp; DESCAMPS M. 1968. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.) 4 (2): 419 - 435." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]" type="journal article" year="1968">Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps (1968)</bibRefCitation>
who limited the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFAF12BFBE70A87D1C1AD9A" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1945" box="[1090,1249,406,433]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauvarovia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendizabali">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFAF12BFBE70A87D1C1AD9A" box="[1090,1249,406,433]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">G. mendizabali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the region north of the Oued Dra valley. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFB300AA7D007ADFB" author="Massa" box="[1173,1319,439,465]" firstAuthor="Massa" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="371 - 396" part="48" refId="ref12636" refString="MASSA B. 2012. - New species, records and synonymies of West Palearctic Pamphaginae (Orthoptera: Caelifera: Pamphaginae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 48 (3 - 4): 371 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2012.10697786" title="New species, records and synonymies of West Palearctic Pamphaginae (Orthoptera: Caelifera: Pamphaginae)" type="journal article" year="2012">Massa (2012)</bibRefCitation>
checked the identity of a male collected at Pozo Mesit (Saquia Al Hamra region, 6.XI.1944, Mateu J. col., MNHN), further extending the distribution of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFAF12BFCE60926D08FAF5A" blockId="14.[810,1456,215,880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFAF12BFCE60926D178AE7B" author="Morales Agacino" box="[835,1112,566,593]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="241 - 283" part="23" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/150020" refId="ref13011" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1947 a. - Notas sobre ortopteroides de Ifni y Sahara Espanol. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 23 (3): 241 - 283. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 150020" title="Notas sobre ortopteroides de Ifni y Sahara Espanol" type="journal article" year="1947" yearSuffix="a">Morales Agacino (1947a)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned eight additional localities for 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFAF12BFC070946D164AE5A" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1945" box="[930,1092,598,624]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauvarovia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendizabali">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFAF12BFC070946D164AE5A" box="[930,1092,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">G. mendizabali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the lower Oued Dra Valley to the Sebkhat Ad-Dame (Rio de Oro bay) over 600 km of coastline: Aserifa (D) = Asrifa, 28°17’24”N, 11°24’37”W; Taruma = Touaroum, 26°46’15”N, 13°30’58”W; Dora = Dawra, 27°25’14”N, 12°59’21”W; Sebja Tah = Sebkhat Tah, 27°41’60”N, 12°48’00”W; Sebja Echaiba = Lajcheb, 27°16’12”N, 13°06’36”W; El Kantara =Al Gantra, 26°03’24”N, 14°04’17”W; Pozo Tuf = Ayn Touf, 24°36’13”N, 14°59’17”W; Sebja Dam = Sebkhat Ad-Dame, 23°55’48”N, 15°35’60”W.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
